J and I have always been very open about our hopes of having more kids but the thought of starting to try again can be stressful at times. Since having Everly my cycle has been all over the place and I feel very lost and frustrated when it comes to tracking as I felt like I wasn’t understanding the full picture of where my body was at. So I wanted to share a product that I just started using that has already given me some confidence and peace of mind about my cycle and fertility.

I have been using @mirafertility as a hormone tracker + as a natural family planning tool and so far it has been amazing and super easy to use. Through tracking, and using the app, I have learned so much about each of the key fertility hormones (E3G, FSH, PG, and LH) and their purpose and how they all interact with each other. What I appreciate the most is that @mirafertility is an at-home test that has 99% lab-grade accuracy. All it takes is 20 mins and all the information syncs with the app for you to monitor and keep track. I would recommend it to anyone who is natural family planning, wants to understand their fertility more or is currently TTC.

Feel free to comment or dm me with any specific questions!

Use the code SAMANTHA25 for 25$ off the Mira Kits & Bundles.

Counting down the days until we get warmer weather ☀️ Our family is on the hunt to find new local coffee shops and cafes that are fun and family friendly! 

When I say family friendly I don’t mean places for kids to play or run wild, I want our babes to learn to enjoy just hanging out over a yummy treat and fun conversations with us. Family friendly for us means, stroller friendly, wide range of treats and affordable! Can’t wait to share what we find around town (Vancouver & surrounding areas). Hopefully we will have a solid list of places to go by mid spring. 🌼

Pictured: Kits Beach Coffee — We LOVE this place but don’t visit it much during the winter as it is a bit small inside so if we don’t find a seat it can be tricky to sit down with the kids but in the spring/summer/fall we like to visit as they have so much seating outside or we walk (5mins) over to the beach. And the kids love the food. This one checks all the boxes for us!

@try_blossom — the only skincare product that C will let us use on his extremely sensitive skin. 

We got this couple months ago right as C went through his month of being sick on and off and his lips got so chapped that he was constantly asking for what he calls his “honey balm” to get some relief. He’s also currently going through a eczema flare up covering his whole back and @try_blossom is all what C is willing to consistently put on throughout the day to help. We’ve tried many products and are relieved to find something that is clean but also that C enjoys using. #gifted & #toddlerapproved

My mom always jokingly complained that when I was young she had to buy me shoes all the time. I didnt really think it was as bad as she made it seem until now. Everly grows very fast and I feel like every month we are at a shoe store or I'm measuring her feet for online purchases. The other day we walked in to our local @littleburgundyshoes and the workers there said “oh hey it's been a couple weeks since we've seen you guys!” 💀 that's how often we buy shoes. Someone tell me I'm not the only one with this issue and tell me your tips and tricks. We do, depending on the style shoe, go a size up but Everly isn't a fan as she has issues climbing up at some parks when the shoes aren't the perfect fit 🙄🤪 

And on a second note, both our kids have very wide feet so the options are very limited. They basically live in converse and birkenstocks. Anyone know other good wide feet friendly brands? 😬

#motherhoodproblems #rantoftheday

"You have been criticizing yourself for years, and it hasn't worked. Try approving of yourself and see what happens." - Louise L. Hay

The last couple of months have been quiet around here for me. It's been a time of learning and unlearning. Motherhood is challenging, and while I knew there would be difficulties, I didn't anticipate that many of them would revolve around my own mental health, self-expectations, self-love, self-forgiveness, and the importance of grace.

“It's okay to be frustrated, tired, or lose your cool. I am only human, and it doesn't mean I am a bad mom." These are just a few of the many affirmations I remind myself of daily. Some days, it's still hard to believe, but I am on a journey, and I am making progress. I am learning to love myself, embracing all my flaws. Prioritizing self-love and my mental well-being is essential so that my children can grow up understanding how to forgive, love themselves, and effectively manage their emotions.

So to any mom who needs to hear this, you're an amazing mom, and it's okay to have a bad day. Remember to be kind to yourself and embrace the journey of motherhood with all its ups and downs. You're doing great!

Life lately 👌🏻 ft. some pretty cute videos that are definitely worth watching. 😏

#thisismotherhood #thislittlelifeofmine #ourmoments #letthembelittle

This month we celebrated FOUR years of loving our sweet boy. 🤍

Christian, we are so proud of you and the little human you've become! We can't wait to watch you continue growing, learning and exploring this beautiful world with us. Love, mommy & daddy.

And yes, we celebrated by a last minute trip to Disneyland and to visit some of our favourite friends. Can't wait to share lots of our first family vacation!

#thislittlelifeofmine #ourmoments #letthembelittle

Disneyland ✨ we decided to take the kids on a semi last minute trip to Disneyland and visit some friends. It was our first ever family vacation travelling on the plane with kids. It was equally chaotic and magical but 100% worth it.

Justin and I hadn’t been since we were kids and even in our thirties the magic was still so real but nothing beat seeing it through our kids’ eyes especially for the first time. Was it a relaxing fun vacation? Absolutely not. Would we do it again? 100%.

happy second birthday to my sweet girl.

Keeping spreading your joy everywhere you go, and don’t let anyone ever put your fire out. 🤍✨

Happy First Day of Summer ☀️

Though summer has only just started (not even really cause it’s super gloomy here currently) I’ve already come to the conclusion that summers are way too short. So we’re eagerly waiting for the sun to come out so we can spend every possible moment outside soaking it all in.

I phrase I use to hear a lot before having kids and occasionally still do is, “Say goodbye to all the things you love” in regards to having kids. “Say goodbye to all those coffee shop dates” or things like “Just wait till you have kids, no more hiking or camping like you use to” “Can’t have nice things anymore”. Well in case you needed to hear this, it’s far from the truth, yes life changes, yes there are ups and downs but no, we didn’t say bye to all the fun things we love doing, we just get to share them with our littles ones now.

ps. Add @nemesis.coffee to your list of kid friendly coffee shops. Good drinks, tasty treats, good space and stroller friendly!

Testing out the sleek and fun Lincoln Corsair with a little family adventure to the city. 

I got to experience the perfect balance of family-friendly features and fun driving modes with the Lincoln Corsair. It’s got a spacious interior, making sure everyone is comfy, for daily commutes or road trips. I also love having the peace of mind with all the advanced safety features on board. 

It’s even really easy and fun to drive, especially when you can easily switch between all the different driving modes to match your mood or the road conditions. I liked how smooth and relaxing the "Comfort" mode felt, although the “Sport” mode was quite eye opening. 🤪 

After a long day out and about we loved being able to drive home in our little sanctuary from the outside world. 

@lincolnca #LincolnCorsair #UnleashTheAdventure #PowerofSanctuary

The Everly beach update that no one asked for: she loves the thought of going to the beach but she still very unsure about sand once she steps foot on it and takes about 2 hours or so to warm up to it - oceans with waves are a no go but tide pools are ok at when she’s in the mood. Let’s hope next summer we make some better progress. 🤪

We've been out of town for almost the entire past month, savoring every bit of summer with the kids and creating lasting memories along with some new traditions. So be warned, I've got a month's worth of memories and photos from four different trips to share. 🤪

Let's kick things off with one of our newfound local favorites. We tried blueberry picking for the first time before heading out of town for August. Honestly, I didn't expect the kids to enjoy it as much as they did, but it turned out to be a fantastic experience. The blueberry bushes were just the right height for the littles. We're already looking forward to some apple picking adventures this fall.

Take this as a sign to plan a trip to Washington’s coast.

Better late than never, I guess, but I’m finally sharing our favorite trip from this summer when we visited a couple of the beautiful beaches in the Pacific Northwest (PNW). It had always been a bucket list item of mine to drive on a beach, and it turned out to be such a fun experience. Even though the weather wasn’t always the warmest, it was still incredibly worth it, and I highly recommend it. As a mom, being able to drive up to the perfect spot on the beach and have all your stuff with you, instead of dragging it and the kids from the parking lot through the sand, was an unreal and glorious experience. I’m sure all the parents out there can relate. 🤪

On this trip, we checked out Ocean Shores and Westport Dunes, which is about a 5-hour drive (with no traffic) from Vancouver. We stayed in an Airbnb in a town located 30 minutes between the two beaches and spent a day at each beach. There is so much to explore in the PNW, and it is stunning; you really can’t go wrong with a vacation anywhere along the coast.

Little tip: If you choose to head down there, just make sure you have a state park pass to enter the park with your vehicle, which you can get online.

New Year, New Pics.

Last year was far from what I imagined it would be, despite making so many good memories we had so many health issues, all 6 of us, from our dog Bo to my mom. It felt like it consumed most of the last half of our year but I’m determined to not let it get the best of us. We have so much to look forward to and I couldn’t be more excited. 

Cheers to not just surviving but thriving 💃🏻
